&                     ------------------------------------
                      | QUEUEING DATASETS TO BE ARCHIVED |
                      ------------------------------------
$
  WHEN A DATASET IS ARCHIVED TO TAPE IT NORMALLY RETAINS THE SAME NAME.  USE OF
  THE&QUALIFIER$CAUSES THE DATASET TO BE RENAMED.  THE VALUE SPECIFIED IS
  INSERTED IMMEDIATELY BEFORE THE LAST NODE OF THE DATASET NAME.  FOR EXAMPLE:
  IF THE QUALIFIER&SMITH$WERE SPECIFIED WHEN ARCHIVING A DATASET NAMED
 &BCPQT.A1007211.CLAIMS$, THE NEW DATASET WOULD BE&BCPQT.A1007211.SMITH.CLAIMS$

  THE&COMMENT$FIELD IS USED TO PLACE ANY USER INFORMATION, UP TO 30 CHARACTERS
  LONG,  INTO THE ASM2 CATALOG.  WHEN INQUIRIES ARE MADE ABOUT ARCHIVED
  DATASETS,  THE COMMENT CAN BE DISPLAYED.


